<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="18.[189,303,267,293]" box="[189,303,267,293]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,267,293]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,267,293]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[189,1399,313,656]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
We tentatively propose the new combination based on the external morphology (although examination of penis morphology is imperative to be certain) of the male type (MNHN) by the following features: (1) outline of dorsal scutum gamma-type; (2) eyes poorly spaced and ocularium without depression (“Mamelon oculaire assez grand, ovale transverse, bas, légèrement granuleux.” 
<bibRefCitation author="Simon E." box="[1106,1250,419,445]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="183 - 241" refId="ref10741" refString="Simon E. 1879. Essai d'une classification des Opiliones Mecostethi. Remarques synonymiques et descriptions d'especes nouvelles. Premiere partie. Annales de la Societe entomologique de Belgique 22: 183 - 241." type="journal article" year="1879">Simon 1879</bibRefCitation>
); (3) areas I– III with paramedian tubercles and (4) dorsal scutum and coxa IV without yellow spots. The impossibility to examine the 
<typeStatus box="[381,484,489,515]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">holotype</typeStatus>
thoroughly and the “doubtful origin” of the specimen described by Simon does not allow us to verify whether this species corresponds to another already described species. It is very difficult to conclude whether the records provided by 
<bibRefCitation author="Roewer C. F." box="[880,1058,560,586]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="527 - 632" refId="ref10651" refString="Roewer C. F. 1928. Weitere Weberknechte II. (2. Erganzung der Weberknechte der Erde, 1923). Abhandlungen des Naturwissenschaftlichen Vereins zu Bremen, 26 (3): 527 - 632." type="journal article" year="1928">Roewer (1928)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Mello-Leitao C. F. de" box="[1115,1355,560,586]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="1 - 505" refId="ref10337" refString="Mello-Leitao C. F. de 1932. Opilioes do Brasil. Revista do Museu Paulista 17 (2): 1 - 505." type="journal article" year="1932">Mello-Leitão (1932)</bibRefCitation>
are correct because both localities match with those of various species of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Coronato &amp; Pintoda-Rocha 2017)" baseAuthorityName="Coronato &amp; Pintoda-Rocha" baseAuthorityYear="2017" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmetidae" genus="Metalibitia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1027,1157,595,621]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Metalibitia</emphasis>
(Coronato &amp; Pintoda-Rocha 2017)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
